						<summary>

						

						<p>Slab lying in a mound in the Sāhebu Bazaar.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1055: 1133 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The details of date given in the record <hi rend="italic">viz.,</hi> Śaka 1055, Āshāḍha ba, Monday, Dakshiṇāyana-saṅkrānti corresponds to 1133 A.D., June 26.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift made by Vāsēna, son of Prōle-nāyaka, for the merit of his father. The nature of gift is not clear.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. X, No. 92.</p>						

